result.name: McDonald's

reviews.text: Went at around 4, not very crowded. Has electronic order to aid me in my anti socialness
Good.

Royal Plaza is a small shopping centre which accompanies the Royal Ascot residential property in Fo Tan. There are a handful of eateries and fast food places at Royal Plaza including a McDonalds. Opening hours 7am to 10pm daily. 

Amongst the normal McD breakfasts, burgers and other regular food and drink items, there is now three Signature Collection options on offer at McDonald's throughout Hong Kong, including this branch at Ascot Plaza. These include two premium beef burgers as well as a chicken sandwich. 

I recently tried the Spicy Chicken Jalapeno Sandwich (HK$40) and found this this to be surprisingly decent. This Signature Collection offer is a buttermilk chicken breast topped with fresh lettuce, grilled onions, spicy relish and jalapenos, served on a brioche bun. The chicken sandwich was surprisingly spicy and flavourful. Fries and drinks served were the same included with the regular meal sets. 

The Signature Collection offers are an interesting addition to the regular food items you can purchase at McDonalds. The price is around twice that of the regular items but it is quite possible that the food is 2-3 times better. 

In the end, McD still represents a budget-friendly and familiar food for western visitors who might be tired of eating local Cantonese food. If you don't mind paying a bit more, try the Signature Collection options. Seems they are much better quality offers.

Ordered McNuggets meal for takeout , staff forgot both the nuggets’ sauce and no single ketchup provided. Don’t understand what’s the point of charging people money for extra sauce and can even forget the sauce within the paid meal.
Cosy most of the time

Nice shopping mall in Fo Tan, relatively close to the MTR. This is in a more luxurious housing development as well, so you can get more expensive, high-quality groceries here. The extra space also makes this place feel more luxurious than an equivalent place close to Central or TST.
It's not a bad little mall. A few places to eat and a good supermarket.
